parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, or even fatalities, as the vehicle may not be able to stop in time or may lose control.
symptoms: The brake pedal travels to the floor
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop
or the ABS and ESC lights come on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes hard to turn
the power steering pump fails
the steering wheel stiffens
and the vehicle is difficult to maneuver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to malfunction, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering wheel remains in an upper position
the steering wheel does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle is difficult to steer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to lose stopping power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle does not stop
and the brake system fails to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the engine can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the vehicle stalls
and the electrical power in the car resets itself.
